Grow up. Harping on a TV release that's free? You got some nerve. 
It's as simple as this for those wondering:

I have a cable provider that uses the more superior modded MPEG4/AVC codec rather than MPEG2.

The cable provider provides broadcasts at 1080i/30FPS, 720p/60FPS, 480i/30FPS, 480p/60FPS.

I can capture any of the above resolutions at 20Mbps max.

My capture device can encode for me live as the broadcast is being aired in Variable Bitrate, or Constant Bitrate.

I set the capture box to encode while airing at 720p at around 7Mbps manually on purpose.

The encode is done when the show is done, so I can upload the files instantly online, and am always the first, and do this so people do not have to wait long, reducing the capture box's encode quality as well so the size isn't too dramatic.

Just as my True Blood rips of the past, I am capable of capturing the original broadcast as aired at 1080i/30FPS, Dolby Digital 5.1 audio @ 384 kbps, but why upload a massive file if I want to get it to everyone fast? Makes no sense to give the real .ts out in that case. 

I cap using a transport stream's container because the only way I can cut ads/commercials out without encoding is using special programs that cut h.264 transport stream files. Basically, I can cut the stream without re-encoding again, leaving the quality and data rate intact. 

For this next episode of Dexter, I've decided to increase the bitrate a bit to enhance the quality of the automatic encode capture. I wasn't pleased with how low of a bitrate I allowed the capture box to use for capturing the show.

Maybe I will also release the true 1080i .ts as I did previously with the last True Blood season after uploading the quick-rip 720p/60FPS encode.

Anyway, valizio007, learn some proper manners, stop being spoiled, and don't assume you know everything. You look like an idiot. Learn to say thank you and if you question something, then ask the question, don't badmouth someone. Your parents should have beat some manners and common sense into you while growing up. Also, don't expect a further reply to anything stupid you have to say. This is the last time.

And to everyone being supportive and complimentary, thank you. I don't have to do this stuff, but I stay at home specifically so I can capture TV for everyone of shows I like as well, giving up my time and my nights, along with my internet for those less privileged to watch it(due to shitty US economy and no cable), or don't even get the show at all in their country. It's nice to hear good feedback, and I will continue capping as I am for all of your enjoyment.
